        <mxCell id="integ-dca-ext" value="External DCA Agencies" style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=#6A1B9A;strokeColor=#4A148C;fontColor=#FFFFFF;fontSize=9;" vertex="1" parent="integ-band">
          <mxGeometry x="1080" y="24" width="140" height="30" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>

        <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════
             CALLOUT BOXES — BLOCKERS + COMPLIANCE
             ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
        <mxCell id="blocker-box" value="&lt;b&gt;⛔ OPEN BLOCKERS — gate integration design lock&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;b&gt;Blocker 1 (Kafka contract):&lt;/b&gt; Abstracted commands (PostPaymentCommand, WriteOffDebtCommand, CreatePaymentPlanCommand) not confirmed as externally publishable. Must verify topic names, payload schemas, response events, consumer-group isolation before DCMS relies on asynchronous financial commands.&lt;br/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;b&gt;Blocker 2 (REST stability):&lt;/b&gt; BFF treats Solon account balance / active suppressions / task state endpoints as stable contracts. Stability guarantees not documented. Must confirm endpoint existence and versioning position before BFF design is locked.&lt;br/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;b&gt;Blocker 3 (MHCM expiry):&lt;/b&gt; SuppressionExpiryJob behaviour for maximumNumberDays=0 undocumented. If 0 = already expired, MHCM suppressions lifted without professional sign-off = breach Reg 21, Debt Respite Scheme Regs 2020 (criminal liability). Mitigation: maxDays=36500 + overrideEndDateSW=true + DCMS-owned release path until source confirmed."
          style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=#FFEBEE;strokeColor=#B71C1C;dashed=1;strokeWidth=3;fontSize=9;verticalAlign=top;align=left;"
          vertex="1" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="20" y="860" width="620" height="210" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>

        <mxCell id="c3-box" value="&lt;b&gt;⚠ C3 COMPLIANCE CONTRADICTION — suspendActiveInstancesSW&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;If = true: Solon auto-suspends BPMN process tokens on suppression creation. Violates RULING-016 §3 guardrails 1 and 4 (voluntary payments, balance recalculation, audit events must continue). Gate-at-effect role is bypassed.&lt;br/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;If = false: Solon records suppression as metadata only. DCMS BreathingSpaceGatingService carries 100% of effect-suppression. Solon native 60-day ceiling enforcement degrades to expiry-record only.&lt;br/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;Both branches are coherent but mutually exclusive. SA must declare the setting per SuppressionType (BREATHING_SPACE, MHCM, vulnerability overlay, internal policy hold) and reconcile with RULING-016 before lock. Cannot be deferred to detailed design."
          style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=#FFEBEE;strokeColor=#B71C1C;dashed=1;strokeWidth=3;fontSize=9;verticalAlign=top;align=left;"
          vertex="1" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="650" y="860" width="480" height="210" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>

        <mxCell id="java-box" value="&lt;b&gt;Java Version Note&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;Option B inherits Solon's JVM: Java 17 documented baseline. Mixing Java 21 bytecode into a Java 17 JVM is not possible. Java 21 mandate → Option C.&lt;br/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;Forward-looking signal (unconfirmed): Solon Tax expected on Java 25 LTS (early May 2026). If confirmed, the Java-version argument for Option C dissolves and Option B strengthens materially.&lt;br/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;Locked against Java 17 baseline until Solon GA release notes confirm otherwise."
          style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=#F3E5F5;strokeColor=#7B1FA2;fontSize=9;verticalAlign=top;align=left;"
          vertex="1" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="1140" y="860" width="494" height="210" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>

        <mxCell id="amplio-box" value="&lt;b&gt;Amplio Authoring Constraints (all DCMS BPMN)&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;1. Parallel Gateway: sequential only — no true concurrent execution&lt;br/&gt;2. Script Tasks: FEEL only — imperative logic in Java delegates&lt;br/&gt;3. Business Rule Tasks: must be Service Tasks (no DMN; use Drools KIE)&lt;br/&gt;4. Compensation events: not implemented — use explicit error boundary paths&lt;br/&gt;5. Only confirmed Kafka topics until Blocker 1 resolved&lt;br/&gt;6. All debtor-facing service tasks must use mandatory gated base class"
          style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=#FFF9C4;strokeColor=#F9A825;fontSize=9;verticalAlign=top;align=left;"
          vertex="1" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="1140" y="860" width="494" height="210" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>

        <!-- Footer -->
        <mxCell id="footer" value="&lt;i&gt;Option B: DCMS is a medium custom layer inside Solon's JVM. Solon provides financial ledger, Amplio, Kafka, Drools, Keycloak/OPA, batch, and observability. DCMS owns DWP BPMN, domain services, dcms schema, and React BFF. Integration design lock requires Blockers 1–3 resolved and suspendActiveInstancesSW declared per suppression type.&lt;/i&gt;"
          style="text;html=1;align=left;verticalAlign=middle;fontSize=9;fontColor=#616161;"
          vertex="1" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="20" y="1076" width="1110" height="30" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>

